00:53:30,720 --> 00:53:31,620
at least locally,

1444
00:53:31,620 --> 00:53:33,500
that it would look flatter to us.

1445
00:53:33,980 --> 00:53:36,400
If the Earth was a marble,

1446
00:53:36,400 --> 00:53:38,380
it would be small,

1447
00:53:38,380 --> 00:53:40,220
but its curvature would be large.

1448
00:53:41,160 --> 00:53:44,890
The curvature of a surface scales

1449
00:53:44,890 --> 00:53:48,620
in a certain way as its radius,

1450
00:53:48,620 --> 00:53:51,680
and in fact it's one over the radius squared.

1451
00:53:51,920 --> 00:53:53,500
The curvature of a sphere,

1452
00:53:53,500 --> 00:53:54,360
for example,

1453
00:53:54,360 --> 00:53:57,020
is one over the radius squared,

1454
00:53:57,020 --> 00:53:59,260
and it either comes in,

1455
00:53:59,260 --> 00:54:01,580
well,

1456
00:54:01,580 --> 00:54:03,780
it's proportional to one over a squared,

1457
00:54:07,420 --> 00:54:08,920
and it either...

1458
00:54:11,080 --> 00:54:14,500
...is positive if space is a sphere,

1459
00:54:14,500 --> 00:54:17,960
zero if space is flat,

1460
00:54:17,960 --> 00:54:21,620
minus one if space is a hyperboloid.

1461
00:54:22,120 --> 00:54:24,760
So it means that there's a k here,

1462
00:54:24,760 --> 00:54:26,880
and k is plus,

1463
00:54:26,880 --> 00:54:27,560
minus,

1464
00:54:27,560 --> 00:54:27,880
one,

1465
00:54:27,880 --> 00:54:28,520
or zero.

1466
00:54:28,860 --> 00:54:31,250
So it's just a placeholder here that tells you

1467
00:54:31,250 --> 00:54:33,640
which of the three kinds of spaces you're talking about.

1468
00:54:35,680 --> 00:54:38,440
This is what Einstein's equations boil down to.

1469
00:54:40,220 --> 00:54:40,940
In fact,

1470
00:54:40,940 --> 00:54:45,040
let's just switch this to the other side.

1471
00:54:46,240 --> 00:54:49,640
Let's just switch it to the other side

1472
00:54:49,640 --> 00:54:53,040
so it becomes minus k over a squared.

1473
00:54:56,700 --> 00:55:01,440
But this equation is absolutely identical to the Newtonian version

1474
00:55:01,440 --> 00:55:06,180
if we think of rho as the mass density for a...

1475
00:55:06,180 --> 00:55:08,540
...it's the equations that we've already explored.

1476
00:55:09,560 --> 00:55:10,200
...it's the equations that we've already explored.

1477
00:55:10,220 --> 00:55:12,710
The only thing new is that we

1478
00:55:12,710 --> 00:55:15,200
now have an interpretation of this term.

1479
00:55:15,280 --> 00:55:16,950
Do you remember what this term

1480
00:55:16,950 --> 00:55:18,620
stood for in the Newtonian example?

1481
00:55:21,780 --> 00:55:24,000
It stood for the energy,

1482
00:55:24,000 --> 00:55:25,680
whether the energy was positive,

1483
00:55:25,680 --> 00:55:26,160
negative,

1484
00:55:26,160 --> 00:55:27,100
or zero.

1485
00:55:27,340 --> 00:55:29,580
It had to do with whether you

1486
00:55:29,580 --> 00:55:31,820
were above or below the escape velocity.

1487
00:55:32,240 --> 00:55:35,720
That's the same exact term here.

1488
00:55:40,760 --> 00:55:43,120
But it has to do with something entirely different,

1489
00:55:43,120 --> 00:55:44,900
or something on the face of it very,

1490
00:55:44,900 --> 00:55:45,460
very different,

1491
00:55:45,460 --> 00:55:47,060
namely the curvature of space.

1492
00:55:48,260 --> 00:55:49,300
Same equation,

1493
00:55:49,300 --> 00:55:53,720
somewhat different physical interpretation.

1494
00:55:55,260 --> 00:55:56,220
You might ask,

1495
00:55:56,220 --> 00:55:58,600
why does this general theory of relativity,

1496
00:55:58,600 --> 00:56:01,470
which contains among other things the

1497
00:56:01,470 --> 00:56:04,340
ingredients of special relativity and so forth,

1498
00:56:04,520 --> 00:56:06,500
why is it the same as Newton's equations?

1499
00:56:07,320 --> 00:56:11,840
And the reason is basically that if you look...

1500
00:56:11,840 --> 00:56:15,180
Let's suppose the universe is curved,

1501
00:56:15,180 --> 00:56:17,120
but we just look on

1502
00:56:17,120 --> 00:56:19,060
a small little piece of it.

1503
00:56:19,240 --> 00:56:21,080
A small little piece of it,

1504
00:56:21,080 --> 00:56:22,540
we can't tell that it's curved,

1505
00:56:22,540 --> 00:56:24,820
but look at all the galaxies in there.

1506
00:56:27,860 --> 00:56:31,210
The way these galaxies move for

1507
00:56:31,210 --> 00:56:34,560
a small enough piece here must be...

1508
00:56:35,400 --> 00:56:39,020
The curvature can't be important for a small enough piece.

1509
00:56:39,280 --> 00:56:42,140
Once we realize that the curvature can't be small enough,

1510
00:56:42,140 --> 00:56:44,680
and that the equations are exactly the same

1511
00:56:44,680 --> 00:56:47,220
for a small piece or a big piece,

1512
00:56:47,420 --> 00:56:50,560
we realize that we

1513
00:56:50,560 --> 00:56:53,700
must somehow reproduce Newton's equations.

1514
00:56:54,000 --> 00:56:55,580
But in any case,

1515
00:56:55,580 --> 00:56:55,840
we do.

1516
00:56:56,160 --> 00:56:59,480
The Newtonian version...

1517
00:57:02,339 --> 00:57:03,020
...is correct.

1518
00:57:04,640 --> 00:57:07,120
But we do have to keep in...

1519
00:57:07,759 --> 00:57:11,200
...and remember that in Newton's physics,

1520
00:57:11,200 --> 00:57:14,520
this stood for the mass density.

1521
00:57:15,660 --> 00:57:17,760
I'm setting the speed of light equal to one,

1522
00:57:17,760 --> 00:57:18,480
so mass,

1523
00:57:18,480 --> 00:57:20,640
E equals mc squared is just E equals m.

1524
00:57:21,160 --> 00:57:22,220
Energy and momentum,

1525
00:57:22,220 --> 00:57:22,980
same units.

1526
00:57:24,900 --> 00:57:28,840
This was the density of ordinary mass,

1527
00:57:28,840 --> 00:57:30,260
ordinary rest mass.

1528
00:57:31,180 --> 00:57:34,240
It was assumed in Newton's equations that everything

1529
00:57:34,240 --> 00:57:37,300
is moving much slower than the speed of light,

1530
00:57:37,500 --> 00:57:39,570
and if I have a collection of particles

1531
00:57:39,570 --> 00:57:41,640
all moving much slower than the speed of light,

1532
00:57:41,860 --> 00:57:45,140
the energy density is just the density of mass.

1533
00:57:46,040 --> 00:57:47,160
On the other hand,

1534
00:57:47,160 --> 00:57:48,760
these equations are more general.

1535
00:57:48,960 --> 00:57:51,100
They follow from Einstein's equations,

1536
00:57:51,100 --> 00:57:52,420
and for example,

1537
00:57:52,420 --> 00:57:55,610
they do apply to situations where particles

1538
00:57:55,610 --> 00:57:58,800
may be moving fast relative to each other.

1539
00:57:58,800 --> 00:57:59,840
In fact,

1540
00:57:59,840 --> 00:58:02,620
they even apply if the energy

1541
00:58:02,620 --> 00:58:05,400
density here is due to photons,

1542
00:58:05,400 --> 00:58:07,980
massless radiation moving with the speed of light.

1543
00:58:08,720 --> 00:58:09,300
So,

1544
00:58:09,300 --> 00:58:11,430
the Newtonian equations wouldn't know

1545
00:58:11,430 --> 00:58:13,560
what to do with photons.

1546
00:58:14,120 --> 00:58:17,020
The Einstein equations know what to do with photons,

1547
00:58:17,020 --> 00:58:17,800
or radiation.

1548
00:58:19,520 --> 00:58:20,620
But otherwise,

1549
00:58:20,620 --> 00:58:22,580
the equations look very similar.

1550
00:58:23,220 --> 00:58:23,940
Okay.

1551
00:58:26,680 --> 00:58:27,040
Yes?

1552
00:58:27,860 --> 00:58:28,580
Um...

1553
00:58:29,540 --> 00:58:30,580
Two questions.

1554
00:58:30,700 --> 00:58:33,250
In that metric where we assume

1555
00:58:33,250 --> 00:58:35,800
that space and time are separated...

1556
00:58:36,580 --> 00:58:36,660
Yes.

1557
00:58:37,360 --> 00:58:39,240
...are we giving any...

1558
00:58:39,240 --> 00:58:42,320
Does that correspond to some physical restriction,

1559
00:58:42,320 --> 00:58:44,680
or is that just the way things are?

1560
00:58:45,040 --> 00:58:45,300
Yeah,

1561
00:58:45,300 --> 00:58:46,060
if you...

1562
00:58:47,000 --> 00:58:53,440
It's a consequence of isotropy and homogeneity.

1563
00:58:54,380 --> 00:58:58,300
If it's isotropic and it stays isotropic,

1564
00:59:00,040 --> 00:59:02,280
and homogeneous and it stays homogeneous,

1565
00:59:02,660 --> 00:59:03,740
there really is no alternative.

1566
00:59:04,420 --> 00:59:05,480
We could prove that,

1567
00:59:05,480 --> 00:59:06,420
but I won't prove it tonight.

1568
00:59:06,640 --> 00:59:08,740
But it is a consequence of that.

1569
00:59:09,240 --> 00:59:09,960
And also,

1570
00:59:09,960 --> 00:59:11,950
why are we focusing on

1571
00:59:11,950 --> 00:59:13,940
the time-time component of that equation?

1572
00:59:14,180 --> 00:59:14,480
Mm-hmm.

1573
00:59:15,580 --> 00:59:17,660
You could actually choose any of them.

1574
00:59:18,580 --> 00:59:19,420
For example,

1575
00:59:19,420 --> 00:59:20,940
you could choose the space-space component.

1576
00:59:22,140 --> 00:59:25,320
What you would get would again be like Newton,

1577
00:59:25,940 --> 00:59:27,600
except instead of being...

1578
00:59:27,600 --> 00:59:30,020
This is the energy equation from Newton.

1579
00:59:30,720 --> 00:59:32,560
It's the F equals mA equation.

1580
00:59:33,330 --> 00:59:37,460
The F equals mA equation does have second time derivatives.

1581
00:59:37,600 --> 00:59:38,700
It has A double dot.

1582
00:59:39,720 --> 00:59:40,480
All right?

1583
00:59:40,820 --> 00:59:42,740
There are a linear combination

1584
00:59:42,740 --> 00:59:44,660
of the space-space and the space-time

1585
00:59:44,660 --> 00:59:46,180
and the time-time equations,

1586
00:59:47,120 --> 00:59:49,660
which instead of looking like the energy equation,

1587
00:59:49,940 --> 00:59:55,080
really do look like the Newton F equals mA equations.

1588
00:59:55,300 --> 00:59:56,040
But they're all equivalent.

1589
00:59:56,040 --> 00:59:57,580
The point is they're all equivalent.

1590
01:00:00,420 --> 01:00:01,780
They better be equivalent.

1591
01:00:03,380 --> 01:00:05,200
Why is it that you don't

1592
01:00:05,200 --> 01:00:07,020
need more than just one of them?

1593
01:00:07,360 --> 01:00:07,880
Well,

1594
01:00:07,880 --> 01:00:09,280
for this simple example,

1595
01:00:09,460 --> 01:00:13,280
there's only one function to calculate.

1596
01:00:13,760 --> 01:00:14,580
It's A of t.

1597
01:00:15,420 --> 01:00:19,460
More general context where geometry may be wavy

1598
01:00:19,460 --> 01:00:21,420
and fluctuate and do other things,

1599
01:00:22,560 --> 01:00:24,640
you may need all of the equations,

1600
01:00:24,640 --> 01:00:26,920
because there are just a lot of functions to compute.

1601
01:00:27,660 --> 01:00:28,100
Here,

1602
01:00:28,100 --> 01:00:28,820
for this case,

1603
01:00:29,180 --> 01:00:31,580
the only unknown is A of t.

1604
01:00:31,700 --> 01:00:32,860
It's only one function,

1605
01:00:33,080 --> 01:00:35,160
and so really you only need one equation.

1606
01:00:35,320 --> 01:00:36,540
You could have picked any one of them.

1607
01:00:37,100 --> 01:00:37,660
All right.

1608
01:00:39,280 --> 01:00:39,720
Good.

1609
01:00:41,260 --> 01:00:45,140
You could not have picked the mixed space-time equations.

1610
01:00:45,900 --> 01:00:48,040
Then you would have just got zero equals zero.

1611
01:00:49,220 --> 01:00:52,040
But if you take the space-space components,

1612
01:00:52,700 --> 01:00:54,400
you'll get the same equations back.

1613
01:00:55,680 --> 01:00:56,280
Okay.

1614
01:00:58,560 --> 01:00:59,160
Okay.

